<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-496-850  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 496 850.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  May 28 1990 n469 p10(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>EC critiques open systems. (European Commission)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Greenbaum, Joshua.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The 'Guidelines for an Informatics Architecture,' a EuropeanCommission report, analyses and criticizes the state of the opensystems market.andP;  The document refers to unavailable products,inadequate standards and unresolved issues such as remote accessto databases.andP;  The report criticizes vendors for professing tosupport open systems while continuing to promote proprietarysystems.andP;  The report also finds fault with open systems for notbeing competitive with proprietary ones.andP;  Applications software,particularly Unix, takes the brunt of the criticism in the report.andO;The report accuses standards bodies of adversely affecting theavailability of standard products and calls for an evolutionarypath between proprietary and open systems.andP;  Additionally, thereport focuses on vendor/user relations rather than user relianceon systems integrators.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Open SystemsStandardsReportsRequirements AnalysisVendor RelationsMarket AnalysisEuropean Community. Commission of the European CommunitiesTrends.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Computing in the European Commission. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>